% Automatisch generiert — Thema: Abortion
% arg/1 Fakten
arg(pro29).  % [pro] The World Health Organization estimated in 2004 that unsafe abortions cause 68,000 maternal deaths worldwide each year.
arg(pro29b).  % [pro] Many of these maternal deaths occur in developing countries where safe and legal abortion services are difficult to access.
arg(pro7).  % [pro] If the State is interested in protecting fetal life after viability, it may go so far as to proscribe abortion during that period, except when it is necessary to preserve the life or health of the mother.
arg(pro71).  % [pro] Americans are more accepting of abortions that occur early in pregnancy when the fetus is not as developed and is not “viable” (able to survive on its own outside of the woman’s body).
arg(pro63).  % [pro] Not all abortions are unjustified.
arg(pro63b).  % [pro] Abortion would be justified if the same justification could be applied to killing an adult human.
arg(pro58).  % [pro] Abortion reduces crime.
arg(pro36).  % [pro] The National Cancer Institute (NCI), the American Cancer Society (ACS), and the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists all refuted the claim that abortion can lead to a higher probability of developing breast cancer.
arg(con140).  % [con] Susan B. Anthony and Elizabeth Cady Stanton led the fight for women’s rights to own property, to vote, and to obtain equal education.
arg(con140b).  % [con] Susan B. Anthony and Elizabeth Cady Stanton spoke out against abortion.
arg(con23).  % [con] I will always support legislation that would end abortion or lead us in the direction of ending abortion.
arg(con152).  % [con] For this reason, I introduced S. 583, the Life at Conception Act on March 14, 2013.
arg(con109).  % [con] The Guttmacher Institute reported that half of all women having abortions each year have had at least one previous abortion.
arg(con109b).  % [con] Eight point five percent of abortions reported to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention in 2010 were performed by women who had three or more previous abortions.
arg(con9).  % [con] Abortion is not permissible from the point at which individual human identity is realized.
arg(con8).  % [con] Fetuses feel pain during the abortion procedure.

% att/2 Fakten  (Dung 1995 — binär; Typ/conf aus LLM-Kandidaten als Kommentar)
att(pro29b, con152).  % [rebuttal] conf=90 — A’s implied conclusion that safe, legal abortion is needed directly contradicts B’s conclusion to enact a law banning abortion from conception
att(pro29b, con9).  % [rebuttal] conf=90 — A argues abortion should be legal to prevent maternal deaths, while B claims abortion is never permissible, making their conclusions mutually exclusive.
att(pro29b, con8).  % [rebuttal] conf=90 — A argues for legal abortion to reduce maternal deaths, directly contradicting B’s claim that abortion should be restricted because fetuses feel pain
att(pro7, con23).  % [rebuttal] conf=85 — A allows abortion when maternal health is at risk, while B claims to always support legislation that ends abortion, implying no such exceptions
att(con152, pro7).  % [rebuttal] conf=80 — B's proposal to ban abortion from conception conflicts with A's conclusion that abortion after viability should be allowed for maternal health, making the conclusions mutually exclusive.
att(pro7, con9).  % [rebuttal] conf=85 — A allows abortion for maternal health after viability, while B claims abortion is never permissible after identity is realized, creating a direct logical conflict.
att(con9, pro71).  % [rebuttal] conf=70 — B claims abortion is impermissible from the point human identity is realized, contradicting A's claim that early abortions are socially accepted.
att(con8, pro71).  % [undermining] conf=80 — B asserts that fetuses feel pain during abortion, challenging A's premise that early abortions are acceptable because the fetus is not viable.
att(con23, pro63).  % [rebuttal] conf=85 — B’s pledge to end abortion opposes A’s assertion that some abortions are justified.
att(con152, pro63).  % [rebuttal] conf=80 — B’s introduction of a “Life at Conception” bill implies all abortions are unjustified, contradicting A’s claim that some are justified.
att(con9, pro63).  % [rebuttal] conf=70 — Con9 asserts all abortions are impermissible after a certain point, contradicting pro63's claim that some abortions are justified.
att(con8, pro63).  % [rebuttal] conf=75 — Con8 claims fetuses feel pain, implying abortions are unjustified, which opposes pro63's assertion that some abortions are justified.
